  "text": "While these numbers cannot be used to infer the correlation between the level of coverage and the occurrence of bugsthe sample is too small, and the bugs collected are biased by the way they are reported-they suggest the limitations of line coverage as a testing metric, with bugs even being introduced by patches with a high coverage. Therefore, even for well-tested code, tools which thoroughly check each program statement for bugs using techniques such as symbolic execution can be useful in practice-for instance, our tool ZESTI [CITATION_1] was specifically designed to enhance existing regression tests to check for corner-case scenarios.",
